snippet.textDisplay: 1:37 - A large reason why fiber has not been built out more to homes is due to many local city areas, in the US, having fiber or alternative internet services effectively banned from entering, by the cable companies.  Cable companies have lobbied regularly to try and cut out competition in much of their locked areas.  There are ways around it, but they are time consuming, can initially be costly (although much of that is the court battle fees), and the cable companies have effectively run campaigns against candidates running for civil and municipal positions that have views contrary to their own.  Look up Seattle's former Mayor Mike McGinn, as one of several instances of this.
